after you made the IDA MCP plugin bind to 0.0.0.0, it became reachable over the network, but the MCP Python SDK now includes DNS-rebinding/Host-header protection that rejects requests whose Host: header isn’t in an allowed list, so curl http://<ip>:13337/... (Host = <ip>:13337) and reverse-proxy traffic (Host = your proxy domain) get a 421/“Invalid Host” even though 127.0.0.1 works; the proxy-side fix is simply to override the Host header that Nginx forwards upstream so IDA always sees a “safe” localhost host (e.g. proxy_set_header Host 127.0.0.1:13337; instead of proxy_set_header Host $host;), which makes the SDK’s host validation pass while you keep external access via the proxy
